in August to assess progress of the peace plan. <PERSON> Arias </PERSON> said <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON> suggested meeting personally with the foreign ministers of <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Guatemala </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Costa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rica </LOCATION> shortly before that summit. `` Now that the truce has been extended 30 days more, I'm sure that we should take advantage of that extension and keep on with the dialoque,'' <PERSON> Arias </PERSON> said. `` I'm sure we can reach a cease-fire soon, and also to advance to real democracy in <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION> really soon. `` There is no better way to resolve the crisis than through negotiations, dialoque,'' <PERSON> Arias </PERSON> said, adding that he had conveyed the same message to <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>. <PERSON> Arias </PERSON> also said he agreed with <PERSON> Shultz </PERSON>' proposal that the secretary of state meet with the four foreign ministers before the summit, tentatively set for Aug. 7 in either <LOCATION> Guatemala </LOCATION> or <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION> would be excluded from the preliminary meeting, but not from the summit itself.
