<HEAD>Human Rights Lawyer Killed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS thruout to UPDATE with human rights groups suggesting
motive in slayings and possible involvement of authorities, new
subversion charges against Europeans, ADD background on Mendoza, no
pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Gunmen pulled a motorcycle beside the car of a human rights lawyer and shot him to death on a downtown street today. <PERSON> Emmanuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Mendoza </PERSON>, 57, was the third human rights lawyer killed in the <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION> in as many weeks. A human rights group today suggested that the police or military could be involved in the unsolved slayings. Police Cpl. <PERSON> Porfirio </PERSON> <PERSON> Olais </PERSON> said two unidentified men on a motorcycle opened fire on <PERSON> Mendoza </PERSON> when he stopped his car at a busy intersection. A bystander brought the lawyer to a nearby hospital, where he died minutes later, police and hospital officials said. <PERSON> Mendoza </PERSON>'s wife, <PERSON> Emilia </PERSON>, said in a radio interview that her husband had received several death threats from unidentified callers. The independent <ORGANIZATION> Philippine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Human </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rights </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Advocates </ORGANIZATION> said <PERSON> Mendoza </PERSON>'s shooting could be related to his work as defense lawyer for slum residents whose communities have been raided by police in search of communist hitmen. <PERSON> Mendoza </PERSON> was a legal counsel of the left-wing BAYAN organization and chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> Manila </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Solidarity </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>, a federation of <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION> slum residents' groups. His killing came two days after a failed assassination attempt on <PERSON> Nemesio </PERSON> <PERSON> Prudente </PERSON>, the left-wing president of the state-run <ORGANIZATION> Polytechnic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> the </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Philippines </ORGANIZATION>. Two weeks ago, gunmen also shot and killed