<BYLINE>By JOHN KING</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 New appraisals of a proposed prison site for which Gov. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>' administration has asked $ 10 million to buy from developers put the value of the land at under $ 6 million, according to sources. The state wants to build a 500-bed prison on the hilltop land in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Braintree </LOCATION>. Developers, who one critic of the project alleges are friends of the Democratic presidential candidate, sought $ 9.5 million for the land two years ago. The <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> is conducting a preliminary inquiry into allegations that the <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> administration leaked word to the developers of state interest in the land. They bought it from a church for $ 3 million. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, who the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> says is not under investigation himself, and the developers deny the allegation or any association with each other. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, asked about the controversy in recent weeks, has reiterated his position that the state will `` not pay one dime more'' than the fair market value of the property. Three sources, all speaking on the condition of anonymity, told <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> on Friday that two appraisals listed the value of the hilltop land in the $ 5 million to $ 6 million range. The sources would not provide exact figures on the appraisals but one said they were `` not far apart.'' The appraisals are being reviewed by a third company, which is scheduled to submit its estimate of the property's worth next week. All three will be used by the state to determine how much to offer for the 782 acres bought by two developers in December 1985. Selection of the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Braintree </LOCATION> site in 1986 by <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> for a medium security prison has been controversial from the outset, with local