<HEAD>Excerpts of Pope's Apostolic Letter</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Vatican-Lefebvre, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The following are excerpts of Pope <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON>'s apostolic letter released Saturday, as translated from Italian by The Associated Press: With great distress the church has observed the illegitimate ordination of bishops performed June 30 by Archbishop <PERSON> Marcel </PERSON> <PERSON> Lefebvre </PERSON>, who made useless years of efforts to assure that the priestly Fraternity of <ORGANIZATION> St. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pius </ORGANIZATION> X ... was in full communion with the church. ... This act of disobedience _ which signifies the outright rejection of the Roman primate _ constitutes a schismatic act. In carrying out this act, despite the formal ` monitum' -LRB- warning -RRB- sent to them by the cardinal prefect of the Congregation for Bishops last June 17, Monsignor <PERSON> Lefebvre </PERSON> and the priests <PERSON> Bernard </PERSON> <PERSON> Fellay </PERSON>, <PERSON> Bernard </PERSON> <PERSON> Tissier </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Mallerais </PERSON>, <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Williamson </PERSON> and <PERSON> Alfonso </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Galarreta </PERSON> have incurred the grave penalty of excommunication as foreseen under ecclesiastical discipline. ... The results of the movement promoted by <PERSON> Monsignor </PERSON> <PERSON> Lefebvre </PERSON> should and ought to be the motive for all Catholics to reflect sincerely on their own faithfulness to the tradition of the church. ... I would also like to call the attention of theologians and other experts in ecclesiastical science, in order that these also feel summoned by the present circumstances. In fact, the ... teachings of the <ORGANIZATION> Second </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Vatican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> call for a renewed examination -LRB- of the faith -RRB-, which brings to light the Council's continuity with the tradition -LRB- of the church -RRB-, especially on those points of doctrine which, perhaps because of their novelty, have not yet been understood well by some sectors in the church. ... Under the present circumstances, I would like above all to appeal solemnly and from the heart, in a fatherly and brotherly way, to all those who have in some way been linked to the movement of Archbishop <PERSON> Lefebvre </PERSON>, so that they understand the serious obligation to remain united with the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION> of Christ in the unity of the <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION>, and not continue to aid that movement in in any way. ... No one should ignore that formal adhesion to the schism constitutes a grave offense to God and leads to excommunication established by the right of the church. ... To all these <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> faithful, who feel close to some older liturgical forms and disciplines of the Latin tradition, I would like to express my will ... to facilitate their spiritual unity with the church, through the means necessary to guarantee respect for their just aspirations. ... Keeping in mind the importance and complexity of the problems referred to in this document, and in virtue of my apostolic authority, I establish the following: a. The creation of a commission, with the responsibility of working with the bishops, the departments of the Roman Curia and interested groups to facilitate complete unification with the church of the priests, seminarians, religious communities or individuals that have been linked to the fraternity founded by <PERSON> Monsignor </PERSON> <PERSON> Lefebvre </PERSON> and who would like to remain united to the successor of <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> in the <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION>, preserving their spiritual and liturgical traditions, in line with the protocol signed last May 5 by Cardinal -LRB- <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> -RRB- <PERSON> Ratzinger </PERSON> -LRB- head of the Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith -RRB- and <PERSON> Monsignor </PERSON> <PERSON> Lefebvre </PERSON>. b. This commission will have a cardinal as its president and be composed of other members of the Roman Curia ... c. Moreover, the spirit of those who feel tied to the Latin liturgical tradition must be respected, through a broad and generous application of the directive ... allowing use of the Roman Missal such the typical edition of 1962.
</TEXT>
