<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Israeli police intercepted a drug pass Saturday when a Lebanese man threw a bundle containing 2.2 pounds of heroin across <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s northern border to a waiting accomplice, a police spokeswoman said. Police in the northern region of <LOCATION> Galilee </LOCATION> arrested the man on the Israeli side of the border, the spokeswoman said. The spokeswoman, who asked not to be identified, said the heroin was worth `` hundreds of thousands of dollars,'' but she could not specify the exact amount. `` Our detectives were scouting the area and they noticed a Lebanese man throwing a package over the border,'' the spokewoman said. `` Then they noticed the ... man waiting for it.'' Israeli police have focused their attention on activity near the border to try to stem the flow of drugs from <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> into <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, the spokeswoman said.
