 A man who killed a woman with a barbecue fork and then set her house on fire while her four children were sleeping has been sentenced to 85 years in prison. <PERSON> Douglas </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON>, 34, was convicted of murder and first-degree arson in the slaying of <PERSON> Kelly </PERSON> <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON>, 28, on March 7, 1987. He was also found guilty of sixth-degree larceny for stealing <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON>'s purse Her children were rescued from the blaze. Superior Court Judge <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hadden </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> on Friday ordered <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> to serve consecutive sentences of life in prison for murder plus 25 years for arson and three months for larceny, the maximum sentence possible. Life is defined as 60 years under state law. <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON>'s body was discovered in the burning home. She had been stabbed more than 60 times. <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> was the last person seen with <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON> the night she was killed. He has an extensive history of assaults and rapes against women, police said.
