<HEAD>Jackson To Take Minority Planks To Floor Of Democratic Convention</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CHARLES J. GANS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Jesse </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> said Saturday he will go to the floor of the Democratic National Convention to push for including a dozen of his policy proposals in the party's platform. `` We ... are determined at this point to take all 12 of our minority planks to the floor in <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> ... in order to inform, inspire and open up the process, to make our convention one of substance,'' <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> said at a news conference on the lawn of his home. The convention's <ORGANIZATION> Platform </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Committee </ORGANIZATION> last week overwhelmingly rejected the planks proposed by <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>, including a call for boosting taxes on the wealthy, freezing defense spending, pledging no first use of nuclear weapons and doubling the money spent on education. `` We will take to the convention ... the kind of program agenda that will expand our party and make us stronger,'' <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> said. Asked whether he thought his decision might divide the party, <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> said that was `` an unfair accusation ... we can have unity without uniformity.'' <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> said he looked forward to discussing the convention and party platform at his Fourth of July meeting in <LOCATION> Boston </LOCATION> with <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>, when the candidates and their wives are to have dinner together and attend a concert. <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> made his remarks after meeting at his home with a group of key advisers, including his campaign chairman, <PERSON> Willie </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION> speaker, platform committee chairwoman <PERSON> Eleanor </PERSON> <PERSON> Holmes </PERSON> <PERSON> Norton </PERSON>, and <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> Fauntroy </PERSON>, the <LOCATION> District </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION>'s