ne tank near the restaurant and noticed that a seam had broken and gasoline was spilling onto the ground. `` The worker went down and advised someone at the restaurant, and they started to evacuate the area,'' he said. The gasoline ignited near the edge of Lake of the Ozarks after the evacuation was in progress and most of the people were out of the restaurant, <PERSON> Glover </PERSON> said. Seconds later, there was an explosion. `` The restaurant and the dock it was on and five boats were destroyed in the explosion and resulting fire,'' <PERSON> Glover </PERSON> said. He said he did not know what caused the explosion. A number of people were found in the water after the explosion, but it was not known whether they were blown into the water by the force of the blast or if they had jumped, he said. Damage from the fire, which was contained about an hour later, were estimated at more than $ 100,000, <PERSON> Glover </PERSON> said. Lake of the Ozarks is a popular resort attraction in central Missouri.
